headline: Farmer's Fridge to offer fresh meals on select Delta flights from LAX
summary: Farmer's Fridge, known for its fresh, machine-vended meals, is partnering with Delta Air Lines to offer a selection of its chef-curated items on select flights. The inflight dining option will launch...

headline: Airlines face 'too much capacity' this summer, analyst says
summary: Summer travel is picking up, but airlines may face turbulence as safety concerns, economic uncertainty, and global trade tensions weigh on the season. Bloomberg Intelligence senior aerospace, defense, and airlines industry analyst George Ferguson joins Market Domination to explain why legacy carriers like Delta (DAL), United (UAL), and American (AAL) are leaning on high-income travelers to support earnings. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here.
